76561198160367841,Recommended,318090,18638086,"Posted: 23 October, 2015",all,Sploder81,"This is a fun little tcg.Currently only single player.Very incomplete, as of this review there are 4 missions to play (I beat them all in 15 mins) and Ive only seen 13 different cards that you can add to your deck. Your max deck size is 15 and you can have 2 of each card in your deck.Your opponents have a wider variety of cards than you but you never get to use them.Also you can aquire different cards from the store during the match but they cant be a part of your core deck when creating a deck.The goal is to get your opponents health to 0.Each player can purchase a draw on each turn provided they have the gold and use these cards to summon monsters, buff your character/monsters or cast a variety of spells using AP which rises by 1 per turn until a max of 7. AP is also used to use hero abilities, each hero has 2 unique abilities.The way the turns are set up is alot like monopoly, you roll dice and can land on;monsters (chose to fight or hire them to work for you),community chest type spaces,a dungeon (beat the monster and add it too your hand),a store to buy a card where you can buy a card to add to your handand another square where you can buy upgrades for your heros statsalso after each lap you gain 100 gold and you get 50 gold for each monster you kill along the way.So in conclusion this is a great game but considering how much content is currently available, this is little more than a demo at this point. I have heard rumors that on full release, this will be a $20 game and honestly if the rest is as good as this, its easily worth the price, assuming they fix some minor bugsI reccomend it, even if you just let it sit in you library until more content comes out."
