76561198053422627,Recommended,318090,18636344,"Posted: 23 October, 2015",all,Zaxtor99 ® YouTube,"Here's my video of one entire game versus the computer AI and a basic explanation of how it works and plays:https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4VUJQOczfOkWow!  There's quite a few of these little dice and card games available, but none of them that I have played are nearly as much fun and as well designed as this game.This game is just early in development when it launched today on October 22, 2015, but it already plays and runs like a finished game with lots of pizazz and glimmer.  This game is as cleverly designed as it's own name of the game is.. ""Dicetiny.. Destiny"" - get it? Hehe.Okay, imagine a board game where you roll dice to move in the opposite direction around the board as your AI opponent, each of you having a goal to knock or see your opponet's health drop to or below 0 health points.  So you take turns rolling the dice to move around, getting more powerful and aquiring more gold every time you pass your starting square on the board (Think Monopoly passing Go rewards).  In the special locations on the board you might land on the temple where you can spend your gold for very nice attack bonuses, health boosts, or action point increases!  Other corners you might land on with your dice roll could be a hand store to buy a very special card to hold in your hand, or a dungeon where you battle an increasingly more difficult monster each time it's defeated, but each also rewarind the winner with more rewards.  There are also trapped locations or occupied spots where you must either fight or hire random creatures to aid you in taking out your opponent.  This game offers a great balance of strategy with all of the choices you make, the gold you spend, when to spend it and what to spend it on, as well as luck with dice rolls and the timing of cards drawn etc.  Think RPG, Magic the gathering, and Monopoly all mixed into a perfect combination with a nice touch of humor and unique artistic style.To be honest, this is a brilliant little game that offers a HUGE bang for your dollar.  You can build your decks, customize your decks, choose and win different cards and heroes, and play a game that will vary so much that each game will ever be the same as the one before.My score even this early in it's development is a very solid and impressive 87%.  Watch my video to get a better understanding of why and how I came up with my score... or better yet just buy this game now and thank me later!  :-)"
